    "Company (most recent first): (1) May 2026 — Lean scaled Pay-by-Bank in the UAE as Open Finance payments went live, processing across FAB, Mashreq, DIB and CBD, and publicising >$100m of card fees saved for clients — the clearest signal that A2A monetisation is moving from pilot to production. (2) 26–27 Mar 2026 — granted the FIRST SAMA Major Payment Institution open-banking licence in KSA, exiting the sandbox into full licensed deployment; notably SAMA licensed a SECOND fintech the same day, so the lead is real but not exclusive. (3) 2026 — public reporting that Lean is broadening beyond open banking and signalling longer-term IPO ambitions (to be tested against undisclosed scale). (4) Mar 2025 — Takamol Ventures extended the Series B (amount undisclosed). (5) Jul 2025 / Nov 2024 — UAE Open Finance IPA, and the $67.5m Series B led by General Catalyst (first GC cheque in KSA), total funding >$100m. Sector: SAMA formalised open-banking licensing under Vision 2030 (Mar 2026); the CBUAE Open Finance regime became mandatory (in force Jul 2025, compliance deadline 16 Sep 2026); Tarabut raised a $32m Series A (Visa, Tiger Global) to push KSA. The synthesis: 2025–26 turned the regulatory thesis from prospective to actual — the rails are now licensed, mandatory and live — while simultaneously confirming that Lean is not the only licensed player and that the value question has shifted decisively to monetisation.",
