      "The G42 ecosystem as captive-plus-anchor demand: e& as standing anchor tenant, G42's own AI compute, and the Stargate UAE cluster give Khazna a demand pipeline that is structurally unavailable to independent operators. It is also the channel through which US-licensed Nvidia capacity (Microsoft $5.2bn/200MW) lands domestically.",
      "Privileged access to US advanced compute: routing Microsoft/Azure GPU capacity and Stargate chips requires the US-assurance relationship G42 has negotiated. A competitor without that standing cannot host frontier AI workloads at scale, regardless of how much shell capacity it builds.",
