    "trajectory": "Consolidating at the top, fragmenting at the edges. Over 3–5 years Khazna's share of installed base is defensible because grid-power and permits gate new supply and its anchor pipeline pre-commits the next tranche of MW. But the back half of the decade brings well-capitalised hyperscale supply (Microsoft self-build optionality, Pure DC, DataVolt) onto the same demand curve; as supply catches the AI-demand spike, lease rates and incremental returns normalise toward global infra levels. The moat protects the existing book and near-term fill; it does not guarantee that the 2028–2030 vintage of MW earns the same economics as today's.",
